This is a Java Maven project.

It is intended to be used by students in Trace Theory classes. It shows how
groups of graph productions can be executed block by block: a block starts,
all productions in that block finish, and only then the next block starts.

Requirements:

* JDK 26
* Maven 3.9 or newer

Build:

    mvn clean package

Run:

    java -jar target/1DMeshParallel-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar

For noncommercial use only.
